The paper deals with algorithms for finding the largest-area inscribed triangle in a convex polygon, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses divide-and-conquer algorithms, which are commonly studied in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper involves geometric concepts such as polygons and triangles, which are relevant to cs.GC (Graphics and Computer Vision). The paper also discusses optimization problems, which are relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
